asked me in a comment if I had a timeline of my fitness journey and I didn’t. So I took the time to do one for all you who follow me and support me. 

Now I try to be as transparent as possible when it comes down to my fitness. This week alone I’ve been getting so many backlash about how I didn’t lose this naturally and how it was impossible. So many disgusting comments and people writing to me in my DM saying that I’m a FRAUD”! I don’t know what makes people think that I am or have them the idea.

Yes I was wearing disposable garments that appear to be the ones people wear when under going surgeries, I had no idea. I went to get a sauna session. Some people said that I wasn’t truthful with my results, nobody here knows me like that personally besides my family and close friends. Y’all decided to follow me because you see some REAL RESULTS! I never faked anything. I’m a real genuine person with a great heart and care for people. 

I tried my best to make this video for those who are losing hope and are struggling forreal.  Get DMs about people who are not mentally in the right state of mind, depressed.

You may not know but I was depressed when I started. I was down I was sad I didn’t love myself, I wanted to eliminate myself from this world. I tried, but my God my Lord and Savior gave me strength and I prayed every day to Him crying to help me. 

I didn’t feel good about myself at all I was the biggest one in my family. Nobody in my family is fat or big. It doesn’t even run in our family. When I gained weight I was in a very tough spot. I was in a relationship that was mentally & emotionally abusive. I was drinking my life away I became an alcoholic and drank my feelings away and the pain I ensured. 

I would go to stores to try things in in H&M and they didn’t fit. I had holes in my pants cause my thighs rubbed together. I was disgusted with myself cause I’d how let myself go so carelessly. Then to hear people say here that I had SURGERY is sooo freaking misleading and absurd.

My story is long, so long I could write a book about it. (One day)

This video represents me! 

I hope I gave you some hope ❤️

👉 Follow @bodysmartfitness for the best mindset, nutrition and fitness tips 
 
👉  Follow @bodysmartfitness 
 
The team at @bodysmartfitness want you to know the truth about diets, nutrition, food, fitness and the mindset hacks that will ensure your success. 
 
😀 We all want to feel good. 
 
😀 We all want to feel happy. 
 
⭐️ We all want to be a success (however success looks for us). 
 
@Bodysmartfitness blend a powerful trilogy of mindset, nutrition and fitness education to help people stop being stuck in a yo-yo cycle of fads and frustration. 
 
🌎 Founded by Jaymie Moran and with a global team of online coaches in the UK, America and Australia, the team coach women to get sustainable results for life without giving up the foods they love. 
 
💬 Jaymie said, "We wanted to start the Body Smart Fitness YouTube channel to give even more people the right science-backed information, inspiration and tools to create lasting results. Basically, we want to give you the TRUTH." 
 
💬 "Nothing gets me more annoyed and frustrated than people remaining stuck in a trap of yo-yo diets and ineffective exercise for years, coupled with a mindset that has been shaped by you thinking you're a failure every time you try and fail a diet. You're not a failure, you have been lied to." 
 
😥 "The diet industry keeps you trapped. My team and I are here to help you break free from that trap." 
 
💪 "Because losing weight is the easy part." 
 
🤯 "It is keeping it off that is hard." 
 
👉 Access @bodysmartfitness YouTube channel via the link in bio. Don't forget to subscribe and click the notification bell so you get first access to the videos.

To get rid of fat deposits on your back, you’ll need to start by creating a caloric deficit. That means that you’ll need to burn more calories during the day than you consume.

In addition to cutting calories, you’ll get rid of back fat more quickly if you focus your exercise routine to target the muscles in your upper and lower back.

Adding high-intensity interval exercise (HIIT) to your routine, along with working out these specific muscles, will start to give you the results that you’re looking for.

Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness for the best nutrition, mindset and fitness tips
.
I can’t even tell you how many times I’ve broken down on my bathroom floor in tears because I saw the number on the scale go up. Or how many times I thought to myself “I’d rather die than gain any more weight.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Little did I know that gaining weight was the BEST thing that’s ever happened to me. If I kept doing what I was doing in 2015, I think I would’ve actually died.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I was exhausted, dehydrated, deprived, starving, depressed, anxious, lost, insecure... and for the sake of what???
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I know now that this is a deeper, cultural issue of fat phobia, the irrational fear or hatred of bigger bodies and it only exists because some big companies realized that if we idealize an unrealistic body, women will spend BILLIONS trying to look like it. 🤷‍♀️
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Knowing that, I practice body acceptance and self-acceptance not just for myself, but for every woman who gets targeted by diet culture.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I embrace my body, at any size, shape and weight, so that you have permission to do the same.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It’s not about me anymore, it’s about all of us. ♥️

node.text:
Stop comparing yourself against images that are filtered 👉🏼 ⁣
⁣
The left picture of me has a preset on which makes the colours blend together and smooths out my skin. ⁣
⁣
The right picture has no preset on and is me just being me. My body, my skin, my cellulite, my stretch marks ... The way we are designed to be 🧡 ⁣
⁣
It’s perfectly okay to add a filter or to pose a certain way to look good, but you need to remember to be okay with the image of yourself that isn’t filtered or posed in the first place. ⁣
⁣
Try being open at accept yourself in every angle, every lighting and every pose, it can help your mindset accept your body and will allow you to be kinder to yourself which we need to practice more of! ⁣
⁣
STOP CHASING PERFECTION BECAUSE PERFECTION DOESN’T EXIST! ✋🏼 ⁣
⁣
Putting pressure on yourself to look perfect all of the time because of the images you see online being filtered and smoothed to look their very best, will slowly drag you down thinking you need to look like that 24/7. ⁣
⁣
Yes it’s nice to add a filter every now and then but what is also good is to appreciate your body and your face without one. ⁣
⁣
Appreciate what your body does for you and appreciate how much your body goes through in order for you to be healthy and thriving daily! ⁣
⁣
Don’t tear yourself down because you’re not what the filter shows, don’t tear yourself down because your skin isn’t perfect or your body isn’t perfect ... ⁣
⁣
Because ... trust me on this .. you don’t need to be perfect to be loved, you just need to show your body the love it truly deserves 🧡⁣ cc: @hayleymadiganfitness
⁣

Follow 👉  @bodysmartfitness for the best mindset, nutrition and fitness tips 👉  Follow @bodysmartfitness  
 
Double tap if agree 🧡 In a world of filters, FaceApp and all those fandangly apps that alter the way reality is perceived, why not spend your time changing your reality for good?⁣ 🤳    
 
👉 There is nothing more miserable than putting a filtered version of yourself out to the world - but then not being able to step in the real world for fear of your fakery being found out. ⁣   
⁣   
Jaymie co - founder @bodysmartfitness said 'We had one client recently who said she had become so reclusive that she really just wanted to make her filtered pictures a reality once and for all.⁣ ' 
⁣   
🙋‍♀️If you want to make your filtered pictures a reality, it is achievable. Unless you’ve turned yourself into some dog or weird rabbit. 
⁣   
💪 Working on your habits is an ongoing process. If you start small and soon you will notice a big difference.⁣  
 
❌ So stop with the filters, well unless they’re just for fun. When you’re using them to hide the real you, that’s not good for your mental health at all.⁣   
⁣   
🙋‍♀️ Be proud of who you are. You don’t need filters to look and feel better.⁣   
⁣   
Looking and feeling better happens naturally when you prioritise your physical and mental health. ⁣   
⁣   
You’ll never need a filter again!⁣
